President Muhammadu Buhari has stated why he stayed clear of the ongoing rift between the governor of Kano State, Abdullahi Ganduje, and Emir of Kano, Muhammadu Sanusi II. The President in a statement by his Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity, Garba Shehu, said the Nigerian constitution bars him from interfering in such matters. 



